                  This data can be interpreted by mapping each number onto the column header it corresponds
                  to and using the row headers to indicate the frequency with which the student writes in each genre
                  for school.
                  
                  These statements can be grouped into the following factors --
                  
                  Factor 1 (achievement/effort):                 
                   I work hard to improve my writing skills.
                   When I write I keep on working no matter how hard it gets.
                   I put a lot of effort into learning how to write better.
                   I set high standards for myself when I write. 

                  Factor 2 (Efficiency):
                   When I write I try to get the task done as quickly as possible.
                   When I write I try to finish as quickly as I can.
                   When I write I try to find easier ways to complete the task.
                   When I write for school the most important thing is completing the assignment.
                
                  Factor 3 (Focus):
                   When I write I try to stay focused and maintain my concentration.
                   When I write I try to keep working and make steady progress.
                   I work hard to avoid making mistakes while I am writing.                     
                   I often write to figure out what I really think.
                   I use my writing to improve my understanding of the subject I am writing about.
                                    
                  Factor 4 (Embarrassment):
                   I am sometimes embarrassed or nervous about my writing.
                   I try to keep my writing private so I won't feel embarrassed about my mistakes.  

                 Factor 5 (Performance):
                   When I write for school I do my best to get good grades. 
                   I try to impress people with my writing.
                   When I write for school I try hard to please my teacher.

                Factor 6 (Communication):
                   I often write in order to express how I feel.
                   I write to communicate with other people.
                   When I write I try to get my ideas across clearly.
                   I often write to convince other people to agree with me.              

                Factor 7 (Agency/Engagement):
                   I choose to write about subjects that I find personally meaningful.
                   I prefer to write about subjects that I choose for myself.
                   I try to write things that other people will want to read.
                   I often try to write things other people will enjoy.

                Remember that typical students have the following profile on each factor --

                   On Factor 1 (achievement/effort), the largest group of students:
                    agree (or strongly agree) that they work hard to improve their writing skills.
                    agree that when they write they keep on working no matter how hard it gets,
                    agree that they put a lot of effort into learning how to write better,
                    agree (or strongly agree) that they set high standards for themselves when they write.

                   On Factor 2 (Efficiency), the largest group of students:
                    agree (or strongly agree) that when they write they try to finish as quickly as they can,
                    agree that when they write they try to get the task done as quickly as possible,
                    agree (or strongly agree) that when they write they try to find easier ways to complete the task,
                    agree that when they write for school the most important thing is completing the assignment.
                  
                  On Factor 3 (Focus), the largest group of students:
                   strongly agree that when they write they try to stay focused and maintain their concentration,
                   agree that when they write they try to keep working and make steady progress,
                   agree that they work hard to avoid making mistakes while they are writing,                   
                   agree that they often write to figure out what they really think,
                   agree that they use their writing to improve their understanding of the subject they am writing about.

                 On Factor 4 (Embarrassment), the largest group of students:
                   agree that they are am sometimes embarrassed or nervous about their writing,
                   agree that they try to keep their writing private so they won't feel embarrassed about their mistakes.                   
          
                 On Factor 5 (Performance), the largest group of students:
                   strongly agree that when they write for school they do their best to get good grades,             
                   agree that when they write for school they try hard to please their teacher,
                   agree that they try to impress people with their writing.

                On Factor 6 (Communication), the largest group of students:
                
                   Agree (or strongly agree) that they often write in order to express how they feel,
                   agree (or strongly agree) that when they write they try to get their ideas across clearly,
                   agree that they write to communicate with other people,
                   disagree that they often write to convince other people to agree with them,

                On Factor 7 (Agency/Engagement), the largest group of students:

                   strongly agree they prefer to write about subjects that they choose for themselves,
                   agree that they choose to write about subjects that they find personally meaningful,
                   agree that they often try to write things other people will enjoy,
                   agree that they try to write things that other people will want to read,

